                <note rend="inline" type="source">824.01/927c: Circular telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Diplomatic Representatives in the American Republics
                            Except Argentina, Bolivia, and Mexico</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-06-15T00:00:00-04:00"
                            >June 15, 1944—midnight</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The Mexican Foreign Minister has advised our Embassy in Mexico City that he has
                    received the report of his representative recently returned from Bolivia which
                    favors recognition. The Foreign Minister states that he is willing to proceed
                    with recognition and suggests the date of June 23 as the date for simultaneous
                    action by the other American republics. The Mexican Foreign Minister has handed
                    a copy of his representative’s report to all the missions in Mexico City except
                    Bolivia and Argentina together with a note setting forth the foregoing
                    information.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
